                            <comment id="376054" author="adilger" created="Wed, 21 Jun 2023 04:03:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I checked back 6 months and this is only failing with &lt;tt&gt;rolling-upgrade-mds-zfs&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;rolling-downgrade-client1-zfs&lt;/tt&gt; (old 2.12 client, new ZFS MDS) though I haven&apos;t looked at why that is the case.  The first failure was 2023-03-24, but this was the &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/search?test_groups%5B%5D=rolling-upgrade-mds-zfs&amp;amp;test_set_script_id=f9516376-32bc-11e0-aaee-52540025f9ae&amp;amp;start_date=2023-01-01&amp;amp;end_date=2023-03-30&amp;amp;source=test_sets#redirect&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;first time that rolling upgrade was run&lt;/a&gt;, so I think the problem predates this time and is not related to a bad patch landing at that time.   The failure is not hit with 2.14.0-2.15.x &lt;tt&gt;rolling-upgrade-mds-zfs&lt;/tt&gt; testing, so it looks like the issue was introduced sometime in the 2.13 or 2.14 development cycle.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
